---
import Base from "../layouts/Base.astro";
import Nav from "../components/Nav.astro";
import Footer from "../components/Footer.astro";

const updated = "April 25, 2026";
---

<Base
  title="Privacy Policy — Dualio"
  description="What Dualio collects, how it's stored, and how to delete it."
>
  <Nav />
  <main class="container legal section">
    <span class="eyebrow">Last updated · {updated}</span>
    <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>

    <p>
      Dualio is a personal memory inbox. We collect only what we need to make
      your saved items work for you across your devices.
    </p>

    <h2>What we store</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>
        Your email address, used only for sign-in.
      </li>
      <li>
        Items you save — links, raw text, screenshots, photos — together with
        their AI-generated metadata (title, summary, type, embeddings).
      </li>
      <li>
        Original images you upload, kept in private object storage with signed
        URLs. Free-tier images are deleted after 30 days unless you keep them
        on a paid tier.
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h2>What we do not do</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>We do not sell or rent your data.</li>
      <li>
        We do not run advertising or behavioural tracking inside the app.
      </li>
      <li>
        We do not share your saved items with anyone other than the AI
        providers required to process them (currently OpenAI for embeddings and
        text/image extraction). These providers process data on our behalf and
        do not train on it.
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Deleting your data</h2>
    <p>
      Inside the app you can delete any saved item at any time. To remove your
      account and everything we have stored on your behalf, email
      <a href="mailto:privacy@dualio.app">privacy@dualio.app</a> from the
      address you used to sign in. We will delete every record and stored file
      tied to your account within 7 days.
    </p>

    <h2>Contact</h2>
    <p>
      Questions about this policy? Write to
      <a href="mailto:privacy@dualio.app">privacy@dualio.app</a>.
    </p>

    <p class="muted small">
      This page is a working draft and will be updated before Dualio leaves
      private beta.
    </p>
  </main>
  <Footer />
</Base>

<style>
  .legal {
    max-width: 720px;
  }

  .legal h2 {
    margin-top: 2em;
  }

  .legal ul {
    padding-left: 1.25em;
    margin: 0 0 1em;
  }

  .legal li {
    margin-bottom: 0.5em;
  }

  .small {
    font-size: 13px;
    margin-top: 3em;
  }
</style>
